73static void applyMnemonicAliases(StringRef &Mnemonic, const FeatureBitset &Features, unsigned VariantID) {
74 switch (VariantID) {
75 case 0:
76 switch (Mnemonic.size()) {
77 default: break;
78 case 5: // 1 string to match.
79 if (memcmp(Mnemonic.data()+0, "cntlz", 5) != 0)
80 break;
81 Mnemonic = "cntlzw"; // "cntlz"
82 return;
83 case 6: // 1 string to match.
84 if (memcmp(Mnemonic.data()+0, "cntlz.", 6) != 0)
85 break;
86 Mnemonic = "cntlzw."; // "cntlz."
87 return;
88 }
89 break;
90 }
91 switch (Mnemonic.size()) {
92 default: break;
93 case 5: // 1 string to match.
94 if (memcmp(Mnemonic.data()+0, "cntlz", 5) != 0)
95 break;
96 Mnemonic = "cntlzw"; // "cntlz"
97 return;
98 case 6: // 1 string to match.
99 if (memcmp(Mnemonic.data()+0, "cntlz.", 6) != 0)
100 break;
101 Mnemonic = "cntlzw."; // "cntlz."
102 return;
103 }

2416void PPCAsmParser::
2417convertToMCInst(unsigned Kind, MCInst &Inst, unsigned Opcode,
2418 const OperandVector &Operands) {
2419 assert(Kind < CVT_NUM_SIGNATURES && "Invalid signature!");
2420 const uint8_t *Converter = ConversionTable[Kind];
2421 unsigned OpIdx;
2422 Inst.setOpcode(Opcode);
2423 for (const uint8_t *p = Converter; *p; p += 2) {
2424 OpIdx = *(p + 1);
2425 switch (*p) {
2426 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid conversion entry!");
2427 case CVT_Reg:
2428 static_cast<PPCOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
2429 break;
2430 case CVT_Tied: {
2431 assert(OpIdx < (size_t)(std::end(TiedAsmOperandTable) -
2432 std::begin(TiedAsmOperandTable)) &&
2433 "Tied operand not found");
2434 unsigned TiedResOpnd = TiedAsmOperandTable[OpIdx][0];
2435 if (TiedResOpnd != (uint8_t)-1)
2436 Inst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(TiedResOpnd));
2437 break;
2438 }
2439 case CVT_95_addRegG8RCOperands:
2440 static_cast<PPCOperand &>(*Operands[OpIdx]).addRegG8RCOperands(Inst, 1);
2441 break;

2835
2836void PPCAsmParser::
2837convertToMapAndConstraints(unsigned Kind,
2838 const OperandVector &Operands) {
2839 assert(Kind < CVT_NUM_SIGNATURES && "Invalid signature!");
2840 unsigned NumMCOperands = 0;
2841 const uint8_t *Converter = ConversionTable[Kind];
2842 for (const uint8_t *p = Converter; *p; p += 2) {
2843 switch (*p) {
2844 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid conversion entry!");
2845 case CVT_Reg:
2846 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
2847 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("r");
2848 ++NumMCOperands;
2849 break;
2850 case CVT_Tied:
2851 ++NumMCOperands;
2852 break;
2853 case CVT_95_addRegG8RCOperands:
2854 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
2855 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("m");
2856 NumMCOperands += 1;
2857 break;
2858 case CVT_95_addTLSRegOperands:
2859 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
2860 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("m");
2861 NumMCOperands += 1;
2862 break;
2863 case CVT_95_addRegGPRCOperands:
2864 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
2865 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("m");
2866 NumMCOperands += 1;
2867 break;
2868 case CVT_95_addRegGPRCNoR0Operands:
2869 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
2870 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("m");
2871 NumMCOperands += 1;
2872 break;
2873 case CVT_95_addS16ImmOperands:
2874 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
2875 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("m");
2876 NumMCOperands += 1;
2877 break;
2878 case CVT_95_addImmOperands:
2879 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
2880 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("m");
2881 NumMCOperands += 1;
2882 break;
2883 case CVT_95_addU16ImmOperands:
2884 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
2885 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("m");
2886 NumMCOperands += 1;
2887 break;
2888 case CVT_95_addBranchTargetOperands:
2889 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
2890 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("m");
2891 NumMCOperands += 1;
2892 break;
2893 case CVT_95_addRegCRBITRCOperands:
2894 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setMCOperandNum(NumMCOperands);
2895 Operands[*(p + 1)]->setConstraint("m");
2896 NumMCOperands += 1;

3625static unsigned getDiagKindFromRegisterClass(MatchClassKind RegisterClass) {

3628
3629static MatchClassKind matchTokenString(StringRef Name) {
3630 switch (Name.size()) {
3631 default: break;
3632 case 1: // 9 strings to match.
3633 switch (Name[0]) {
3634 default: break;
3635 case '.': // 1 string to match.
3636 return MCK__DOT_; // "."
3637 case '0': // 1 string to match.
3638 return MCK_0; // "0"
3639 case '1': // 1 string to match.
3640 return MCK_1; // "1"
3641 case '2': // 1 string to match.
3642 return MCK_2; // "2"
3643 case '3': // 1 string to match.
3644 return MCK_3; // "3"
3645 case '4': // 1 string to match.
3646 return MCK_4; // "4"
3647 case '5': // 1 string to match.
3648 return MCK_5; // "5"
3649 case '6': // 1 string to match.
3650 return MCK_6; // "6"
3651 case '7': // 1 string to match.
3652 return MCK_7; // "7"
3653 }
3654 break;
3655 case 3: // 1 string to match.
3656 if (memcmp(Name.data()+0, "crD", 3) != 0)
3657 break;
3658 return MCK_crD; // "crD"
3659 }
3660 return InvalidMatchClass;
3661}
3662
3663/// isSubclass - Compute whether \p A is a subclass of \p B.
3664static bool isSubclass(MatchClassKind A, MatchClassKind B) {
3665 if (A == B)
3666 return true;
3667
3668 switch (A) {
3669 default:
3670 return false;
3671
3672 case MCK_Reg36:
3673 switch (B) {
3674 default: return false;
3675 case MCK_Reg37: return true;
3676 case MCK_UACCRC: return true;
3677 }
3678
3679 case MCK_Reg33:
3680 switch (B) {
3681 default: return false;
3682 case MCK_Reg34: return true;
3683 case MCK_ACCRC: return true;
3684 }
3685
3686 case MCK_Reg37:
3687 return B == MCK_UACCRC;
3688
3689 case MCK_Reg34:
3690 return B == MCK_ACCRC;
3691
3692 case MCK_Reg21:
3693 switch (B) {
3694 default: return false;
3695 case MCK_Reg22: return true;
3696 case MCK_Reg24: return true;
3697 case MCK_VSRpRC: return true;
3698 }
3699
3700 case MCK_Reg25:
3701 switch (B) {
3702 default: return false;
3703 case MCK_Reg26: return true;
3704 case MCK_Reg24: return true;
3705 case MCK_VSRpRC: return true;
3706 }
3707
3708 case MCK_Reg19:
3709 switch (B) {
3710 default: return false;
3711 case MCK_VSLRC: return true;
3712 case MCK_Reg18: return true;
3713 case MCK_VSRC: return true;
3714 }
3715
3716 case MCK_Reg9:
3717 switch (B) {
3718 default: return false;
3719 case MCK_F4RC: return true;
3720 case MCK_Reg12: return true;
3721 case MCK_VSSRC: return true;
3722 case MCK_SPILLTOVSRRC: return true;
3723 }
3724
3725 case MCK_Reg26:
3726 return B == MCK_VSRpRC;
3727
3728 case MCK_Reg22:
3729 return B == MCK_VSRpRC;
3730
3731 case MCK_Reg24:
3732 return B == MCK_VSRpRC;
3733
3734 case MCK_Reg15:
3735 switch (B) {
3736 default: return false;
3737 case MCK_VRRC: return true;
3738 case MCK_Reg18: return true;
3739 case MCK_VSRC: return true;
3740 }
3741
3742 case MCK_Reg13:
3743 switch (B) {
3744 default: return false;
3745 case MCK_VFRC: return true;
3746 case MCK_Reg12: return true;
3747 case MCK_VSSRC: return true;
3748 case MCK_SPILLTOVSRRC: return true;
3749 }
3750
3751 case MCK_Reg8:
3752 return B == MCK_SPERC;
3753
3754 case MCK_F4RC:
3755 return B == MCK_VSSRC;
3756
3757 case MCK_VFRC:
3758 return B == MCK_VSSRC;
3759
3760 case MCK_VRRC:
3761 return B == MCK_VSRC;
3762
3763 case MCK_VSLRC:
3764 return B == MCK_VSRC;
3765
3766 case MCK_Reg6:
3767 switch (B) {
3768 default: return false;
3769 case MCK_G8RC: return true;
3770 case MCK_G8RC_NOX0: return true;
3771 case MCK_SPILLTOVSRRC: return true;
3772 }
3773
3774 case MCK_Reg2:
3775 switch (B) {
3776 default: return false;
3777 case MCK_GPRC: return true;
3778 case MCK_GPRC_NOR0: return true;
3779 }
3780
3781 case MCK_Reg18:
3782 return B == MCK_VSRC;
3783
3784 case MCK_Reg12:
3785 switch (B) {
3786 default: return false;
3787 case MCK_VSSRC: return true;
3788 case MCK_SPILLTOVSRRC: return true;
3789 }
3790
3791 case MCK_G8RC:
3792 return B == MCK_SPILLTOVSRRC;
3793 }
3794}

3796static unsigned validateOperandClass(MCParsedAsmOperand &GOp, MatchClassKind Kind) {
3797 PPCOperand &Operand = (PPCOperand &)GOp;
3798 if (Kind == InvalidMatchClass)
3799 return MCTargetAsmParser::Match_InvalidOperand;
3800
3801 if (Operand.isToken() && Kind <= MCK_LAST_TOKEN)
3802 return isSubclass(matchTokenString(Operand.getToken()), Kind) ?
3803 MCTargetAsmParser::Match_Success :
3804 MCTargetAsmParser::Match_InvalidOperand;
3805
3806 switch (Kind) {
3807 default: break;
3808 // 'Imm' class
3809 case MCK_Imm: {
3810 DiagnosticPredicate DP(Operand.isImm());
3811 if (DP.isMatch())
3812 return MCTargetAsmParser::Match_Success;
3813 break;
3814 }
3815 // 'ATBitsAsHint' class
3816 case MCK_ATBitsAsHint: {
3817 DiagnosticPredicate DP(Operand.isATBitsAsHint());
3818 if (DP.isMatch())
3819 return MCTargetAsmParser::Match_Success;
3820 break;
3821 }
3822 // 'CRBitMask' class
3823 case MCK_CRBitMask: {
3824 DiagnosticPredicate DP(Operand.isCRBitMask());
3825 if (DP.isMatch())
3826 return MCTargetAsmParser::Match_Success;
3827 break;
3828 }
3829 // 'CondBr' class
3830 case MCK_CondBr: {
3831 DiagnosticPredicate DP(Operand.isCondBr());
3832 if (DP.isMatch())
3833 return MCTargetAsmParser::Match_Success;
3834 break;
3835 }

4471 case PPC::ACC0: OpKind = MCK_Reg33; break;
4472 case PPC::ACC1: OpKind = MCK_Reg33; break;
4473 case PPC::ACC2: OpKind = MCK_Reg33; break;
4474 case PPC::ACC3: OpKind = MCK_Reg34; break;
4475 case PPC::ACC4: OpKind = MCK_ACCRC; break;
4476 case PPC::ACC5: OpKind = MCK_ACCRC; break;
4477 case PPC::ACC6: OpKind = MCK_ACCRC; break;
4478 case PPC::ACC7: OpKind = MCK_ACCRC; break;
4479 case PPC::UACC0: OpKind = MCK_Reg36; break;
4480 case PPC::UACC1: OpKind = MCK_Reg36; break;
4481 case PPC::UACC2: OpKind = MCK_Reg36; break;
4482 case PPC::UACC3: OpKind = MCK_Reg37; break;
4483 case PPC::UACC4: OpKind = MCK_UACCRC; break;
4484 case PPC::UACC5: OpKind = MCK_UACCRC; break;
4485 case PPC::UACC6: OpKind = MCK_UACCRC; break;
4486 case PPC::UACC7: OpKind = MCK_UACCRC; break;
4487 }
4488 return isSubclass(OpKind, Kind) ? (unsigned)MCTargetAsmParser::Match_Success :
4489 getDiagKindFromRegisterClass(Kind);
4490 }
4491
4492 if (Kind > MCK_LAST_TOKEN && Kind <= MCK_LAST_REGISTER)
4493 return getDiagKindFromRegisterClass(Kind);
4494
4495 return MCTargetAsmParser::Match_InvalidOperand;
4496}

4608FeatureBitset PPCAsmParser::
4609ComputeAvailableFeatures(const FeatureBitset &FB) const {
4610 FeatureBitset Features;
4611 if ((!FB[PPC::AIXOS] || FB[PPC::FeatureModernAIXAs]))

4614}
4615
4616static bool checkAsmTiedOperandConstraints(const PPCAsmParser&AsmParser,
4617 unsigned Kind,
4618 const OperandVector &Operands,
4619 uint64_t &ErrorInfo) {
4620 assert(Kind < CVT_NUM_SIGNATURES && "Invalid signature!");
4621 const uint8_t *Converter = ConversionTable[Kind];
4622 for (const uint8_t *p = Converter; *p; p += 2) {
4623 switch (*p) {
4624 case CVT_Tied: {
4625 unsigned OpIdx = *(p + 1);
4626 assert(OpIdx < (size_t)(std::end(TiedAsmOperandTable) -
4627 std::begin(TiedAsmOperandTable)) &&
4628 "Tied operand not found");
4629 unsigned OpndNum1 = TiedAsmOperandTable[OpIdx][1];
4630 unsigned OpndNum2 = TiedAsmOperandTable[OpIdx][2];
4631 if (OpndNum1 != OpndNum2) {
4632 auto &SrcOp1 = Operands[OpndNum1];
4633 auto &SrcOp2 = Operands[OpndNum2];
4634 if (SrcOp1->isReg() && SrcOp2->isReg()) {
4635 if (!AsmParser.regsEqual(*SrcOp1, *SrcOp2)) {
4636 ErrorInfo = OpndNum2;
4637 return false;
4638 }
4639 }
4640 }
4641 break;
4642 }
4643 default:
4644 break;
4645 }
4646 }
4647 return true;
4648}

4964 struct MatchEntry {
4965 uint16_t Mnemonic;
4966 uint16_t Opcode;
4967 uint16_t ConvertFn;
4968 uint8_t RequiredFeaturesIdx;
4969 uint8_t Classes[6];
4970 StringRef getMnemonic() const {
4971 return StringRef(MnemonicTable + Mnemonic + 1,
4972 MnemonicTable[Mnemonic]);
4973 }
4974 };

4976 // Predicate for searching for an opcode.
4977 struct LessOpcode {
4978 bool operator()(const MatchEntry &LHS, StringRef RHS) {
4979 return LHS.getMnemonic() < RHS;
4980 }
4981 bool operator()(StringRef LHS, const MatchEntry &RHS) {
4982 return LHS < RHS.getMnemonic();
4983 }
4984 bool operator()(const MatchEntry &LHS, const MatchEntry &RHS) {
4985 return LHS.getMnemonic() < RHS.getMnemonic();
4986 }
4987 };

7782#include "llvm/Support/Debug.h"
7783#include "llvm/Support/Format.h"
7784
7785unsigned PPCAsmParser::
7786MatchInstructionImpl(const OperandVector &Operands,
7787 MCInst &Inst,
7788 uint64_t &ErrorInfo,
7789 FeatureBitset &MissingFeatures,
7790 bool matchingInlineAsm, unsigned VariantID) {
7791 // Eliminate obvious mismatches.
7792 if (Operands.size() > 7) {
7793 ErrorInfo = 7;
7794 return Match_InvalidOperand;
7795 }
7796
7797 // Get the current feature set.
7798 const FeatureBitset &AvailableFeatures = getAvailableFeatures();
7799
7800 // Get the instruction mnemonic, which is the first token.
7801 StringRef Mnemonic = ((PPCOperand &)*Operands[0]).getToken();
7802
7803 // Process all MnemonicAliases to remap the mnemonic.
7804 applyMnemonicAliases(Mnemonic, AvailableFeatures, VariantID);
7805
7806 // Some state to try to produce better error messages.
7807 bool HadMatchOtherThanFeatures = false;
7808 bool HadMatchOtherThanPredicate = false;
7809 unsigned RetCode = Match_InvalidOperand;
7810 MissingFeatures.set();
7811 // Set ErrorInfo to the operand that mismatches if it is
7812 // wrong for all instances of the instruction.
7813 ErrorInfo = ~0ULL;
7814 // Find the appropriate table for this asm variant.
7815 const MatchEntry *Start, *End;
7816 switch (VariantID) {
7817 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid variant!");
7818 case 0: Start = std::begin(MatchTable0); End = std::end(MatchTable0); break;
7819 }
7820 // Search the table.
7821 auto MnemonicRange = std::equal_range(Start, End, Mnemonic, LessOpcode());
7822
7823 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "AsmMatcher: found " <<
7824 std::distance(MnemonicRange.first, MnemonicRange.second) <<
7825 " encodings with mnemonic '" << Mnemonic << "'\n");
7826
7827 // Return a more specific error code if no mnemonics match.
7828 if (MnemonicRange.first == MnemonicRange.second)
7829 return Match_MnemonicFail;
7830
7831 for (const MatchEntry *it = MnemonicRange.first, *ie = MnemonicRange.second;
7832 it != ie; ++it) {
7833 const FeatureBitset &RequiredFeatures = FeatureBitsets[it->RequiredFeaturesIdx];
7834 bool HasRequiredFeatures =
7835 (AvailableFeatures & RequiredFeatures) == RequiredFeatures;
7836 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "Trying to match opcode "
7837 << MII.getName(it->Opcode) << "\n");
7838 // equal_range guarantees that instruction mnemonic matches.
7839 assert(Mnemonic == it->getMnemonic());
7840 bool OperandsValid = true;
7841 for (unsigned FormalIdx = 0, ActualIdx = 1; FormalIdx != 6; ++FormalIdx) {
7842 auto Formal = static_cast<MatchClassKind>(it->Classes[FormalIdx]);
7843 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher",
7844 dbgs() << " Matching formal operand class " << getMatchClassName(Formal)
7845 << " against actual operand at index " << ActualIdx);
7846 if (ActualIdx < Operands.size())
7847 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << " (";
7848 Operands[ActualIdx]->print(dbgs()); dbgs() << "): ");
7849 else
7850 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << ": ");
7851 if (ActualIdx >= Operands.size()) {
7852 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "actual operand index out of range ");
7853 OperandsValid = (Formal == InvalidMatchClass) || isSubclass(Formal, OptionalMatchClass);
7854 if (!OperandsValid) ErrorInfo = ActualIdx;
7855 break;
7856 }
7857 MCParsedAsmOperand &Actual = *Operands[ActualIdx];
7858 unsigned Diag = validateOperandClass(Actual, Formal);
7859 if (Diag == Match_Success) {
7860 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher",
7861 dbgs() << "match success using generic matcher\n");
7862 ++ActualIdx;
7863 continue;
7864 }
7865 // If the generic handler indicates an invalid operand
7866 // failure, check for a special case.
7867 if (Diag != Match_Success) {
7868 unsigned TargetDiag = validateTargetOperandClass(Actual, Formal);
7869 if (TargetDiag == Match_Success) {
7870 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher",
7871 dbgs() << "match success using target matcher\n");
7872 ++ActualIdx;
7873 continue;
7874 }
7875 // If the target matcher returned a specific error code use
7876 // that, else use the one from the generic matcher.
7877 if (TargetDiag != Match_InvalidOperand && HasRequiredFeatures)
7878 Diag = TargetDiag;
7879 }
7880 // If current formal operand wasn't matched and it is optional
7881 // then try to match next formal operand
7882 if (Diag == Match_InvalidOperand && isSubclass(Formal, OptionalMatchClass)) {
7883 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "ignoring optional operand\n");
7884 continue;
7885 }
7886 // If this operand is broken for all of the instances of this
7887 // mnemonic, keep track of it so we can report loc info.
7888 // If we already had a match that only failed due to a
7889 // target predicate, that diagnostic is preferred.
7890 if (!HadMatchOtherThanPredicate &&
7891 (it == MnemonicRange.first || ErrorInfo <= ActualIdx)) {
7892 if (HasRequiredFeatures && (ErrorInfo != ActualIdx || Diag != Match_InvalidOperand))
7893 RetCode = Diag;
7894 ErrorInfo = ActualIdx;
7895 }
7896 // Otherwise, just reject this instance of the mnemonic.
7897 OperandsValid = false;
7898 break;
7899 }
7900
7901 if (!OperandsValid) {
7902 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "Opcode result: multiple "
7903 "operand mismatches, ignoring "
7904 "this opcode\n");
7905 continue;
7906 }
7907 if (!HasRequiredFeatures) {
7908 HadMatchOtherThanFeatures = true;
7909 FeatureBitset NewMissingFeatures = RequiredFeatures & ~AvailableFeatures;
7910 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "Missing target features:";
7911 for (unsigned I = 0, E = NewMissingFeatures.size(); I != E; ++I)
7912 if (NewMissingFeatures[I])
7913 dbgs() << ' ' << I;
7914 dbgs() << "\n");
7915 if (NewMissingFeatures.count() <=
7916 MissingFeatures.count())
7917 MissingFeatures = NewMissingFeatures;
7918 continue;
7919 }
7920
7921 Inst.clear();
7922
7923 Inst.setOpcode(it->Opcode);
7924 // We have a potential match but have not rendered the operands.
7925 // Check the target predicate to handle any context sensitive
7926 // constraints.
7927 // For example, Ties that are referenced multiple times must be
7928 // checked here to ensure the input is the same for each match
7929 // constraints. If we leave it any later the ties will have been
7930 // canonicalized
7931 unsigned MatchResult;
7932 if ((MatchResult = checkEarlyTargetMatchPredicate(Inst, Operands)) != Match_Success) {
7933 Inst.clear();
7934 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(
7935 "asm-matcher",
7936 dbgs() << "Early target match predicate failed with diag code "
7937 << MatchResult << "\n");
7938 RetCode = MatchResult;
7939 HadMatchOtherThanPredicate = true;
7940 continue;
7941 }
7942
7943 if (matchingInlineAsm) {
7944 convertToMapAndConstraints(it->ConvertFn, Operands);
7945 if (!checkAsmTiedOperandConstraints(*this, it->ConvertFn, Operands, ErrorInfo))
7946 return Match_InvalidTiedOperand;
7947
7948 return Match_Success;
7949 }
7950
7951 // We have selected a definite instruction, convert the parsed
7952 // operands into the appropriate MCInst.
7953 convertToMCInst(it->ConvertFn, Inst, it->Opcode, Operands);
7954
7955 // We have a potential match. Check the target predicate to
7956 // handle any context sensitive constraints.
7957 if ((MatchResult = checkTargetMatchPredicate(Inst)) != Match_Success) {
7958 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher",
7959 dbgs() << "Target match predicate failed with diag code "
7960 << MatchResult << "\n");
7961 Inst.clear();
7962 RetCode = MatchResult;
7963 HadMatchOtherThanPredicate = true;
7964 continue;
7965 }
7966
7967 std::string Info;
7968 if (!getParser().getTargetParser().
7969 getTargetOptions().MCNoDeprecatedWarn &&
7970 MII.getDeprecatedInfo(Inst, getSTI(), Info)) {
7971 SMLoc Loc = ((PPCOperand &)*Operands[0]).getStartLoc();
7972 getParser().Warning(Loc, Info, None);
7973 }
7974 if (!checkAsmTiedOperandConstraints(*this, it->ConvertFn, Operands, ErrorInfo))
7975 return Match_InvalidTiedOperand;
7976
7977 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(
7978 "asm-matcher",
7979 dbgs() << "Opcode result: complete match, selecting this opcode\n");
7980 return Match_Success;
7981 }
7982
7983 // Okay, we had no match. Try to return a useful error code.
7984 if (HadMatchOtherThanPredicate || !HadMatchOtherThanFeatures)
7985 return RetCode;
7986
7987 ErrorInfo = 0;
7988 return Match_MissingFeature;
7989}
7990
7991#endif // GET_MATCHER_IMPLEMENTATION

7994#ifdef GET_MNEMONIC_SPELL_CHECKER
7995#undef GET_MNEMONIC_SPELL_CHECKER
7996
7997static std::string PPCMnemonicSpellCheck(StringRef S, const FeatureBitset &FBS, unsigned VariantID) {
7998 const unsigned MaxEditDist = 2;
7999 std::vector<StringRef> Candidates;
8000 StringRef Prev = "";
8001
8002 // Find the appropriate table for this asm variant.
8003 const MatchEntry *Start, *End;
8004 switch (VariantID) {
8005 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid variant!");
8006 case 0: Start = std::begin(MatchTable0); End = std::end(MatchTable0); break;
8007 }
8008
8009 for (auto I = Start; I < End; I++) {
8010 // Ignore unsupported instructions.
8011 const FeatureBitset &RequiredFeatures = FeatureBitsets[I->RequiredFeaturesIdx];
8012 if ((FBS & RequiredFeatures) != RequiredFeatures)
8013 continue;
8014
8015 StringRef T = I->getMnemonic();
8016 // Avoid recomputing the edit distance for the same string.
8017 if (T.equals(Prev))
8018 continue;
8019
8020 Prev = T;
8021 unsigned Dist = S.edit_distance(T, false, MaxEditDist);
8022 if (Dist <= MaxEditDist)
8023 Candidates.push_back(T);
8024 }
8025
8026 if (Candidates.empty())
8027 return "";
8028
8029 std::string Res = ", did you mean: ";
8030 unsigned i = 0;
8031 for (; i < Candidates.size() - 1; i++)
8032 Res += Candidates[i].str() + ", ";
8033 return Res + Candidates[i].str() + "?";
8034}
8035
8036#endif // GET_MNEMONIC_SPELL_CHECKER

8039#ifdef GET_MNEMONIC_CHECKER
8040#undef GET_MNEMONIC_CHECKER
8041
8042static bool PPCCheckMnemonic(StringRef Mnemonic,
8043 const FeatureBitset &AvailableFeatures,
8044 unsigned VariantID) {
8045 // Process all MnemonicAliases to remap the mnemonic.
8046 applyMnemonicAliases(Mnemonic, AvailableFeatures, VariantID);
8047
8048 // Find the appropriate table for this asm variant.
8049 const MatchEntry *Start, *End;
8050 switch (VariantID) {
8051 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid variant!");
8052 case 0: Start = std::begin(MatchTable0); End = std::end(MatchTable0); break;
8053 }
8054
8055 // Search the table.
8056 auto MnemonicRange = std::equal_range(Start, End, Mnemonic, LessOpcode());
8057
8058 if (MnemonicRange.first == MnemonicRange.second)
8059 return false;
8060
8061 for (const MatchEntry *it = MnemonicRange.first, *ie = MnemonicRange.second;
8062 it != ie; ++it) {
8063 const FeatureBitset &RequiredFeatures =
8064 FeatureBitsets[it->RequiredFeaturesIdx];
8065 if ((AvailableFeatures & RequiredFeatures) == RequiredFeatures)
8066 return true;
8067 }
8068 return false;
8069}

8071#endif // GET_MNEMONIC_CHECKER
